units.description: New 2025 Forest River RV Wildwood Lodge 42QBQ
units.details:
Forest River Wildwood Lodge destination trailer 42QBQ highlights:

  • Spacious Bunkhouse Suite
  • Queen Bed with Versa-Tilt
  • Three Entry Doors
  • Full and Half Bath
  • Tri-Fold Sofa
  • Outdoor Kitchen

 

The spacious bunkhouse suite on this Wildwood Lodge destination trailer is going to be the ultimate attraction! Because of the opposing slides, there is plenty of room for your kids or guests to truly enjoy themselves, and the dual bunkhouse closets will provide lots of space for their belongings. There are three bunk beds and a Versa Queen bunk in this space, and the half bathroom is also attached to this bunkhouse. The main living area has a tri-fold sofa and free-standing table with chairs, plus a ceiling fan to help keep air moving. The entertainment center has a fireplace, and the kitchen has a residential refrigerator for storing lots of perishables.

 

You just can't beat the Forest River Wildwood Lodge destination trailer! These trailers create the perfect camping destination in and of themselves. There is a new retro/metal redesign that is sure to turn heads at the campground, and the heated and enclosed Accessibelly provides added protection against the elements. Each model includes stainless steel kitchen appliances, a central vacuum with a sweep attachment, a Serta mattress, and kitchen backsplash to name a few comforts. Additional stand-out features include TFL cabinet doors, LED "Blade Lighting' under the awning, stylish roller shades, plus Lippert On-The-Go ladder prep for the option to add a ladder.

units.description: New 2025 Forest River RV Wildwood Grand Lodge 42VERANDA
units.details:
Forest River Wildwood Grand Lodge destination trailer 42VERANDA highlights:

  • Rear Porch/Veranda
  • Kitchen Island with Chairs
  • Spacious Full Bath
  • Versa-Tilt Custom King Bed
  • Outdoor Cooktop and Sink
  • Gel Coat Fiberglass Exterior

 

One look at this destination trailer and you'll be sold! The rear porch/veranda includes an outdoor kitchen with a cooktop and sink plus a ceiling fan so you can sit out back and visit with friends. The L-shaped sofa with an ottoman inside will provide cozy seating space, especially with the fireplace right across the room. Your crew can dine at the kitchen island with four chairs, and there is a large pantry where snacks can be kept for game night. When it's time to call it a night, the front private bedroom with a Versa-Tilt custom king bed is sure to bring comfort, and there is a dresser and wardrobe for your things. A third wardrobe includes washer and dryer prep if you choose to add those appliances. Any guests that aren't sleeping on the sofa can sleep in the loft with a queen bed, large front cabinet with shelves, and an additional cabinet for storage. You will also find a table with space below for your feet, so the kids can color, eat, and play games!

 

With any Wildwood Grand Lodge destination trailer by Forest River, you can enjoy extended stays wherever you go! There is 4K awning blade lighting outside, along with slide out awning toppers, plus a heated and enclosed Accessibelly for added protection. Inside, you'll love the stylish backsplash update, elegant curtain rods and curtains, TFL black walnut entertainment shelves, and stainless steel kitchen appliances. A Serta mattress in the bedroom(s) will provide comfort to each journey, and there is a tankless water heater for hot water when you need it.

units.details:
Live Large in the 2026 Alliance Benchmark 42LFT Destination Trailer
Designed with extended stays and full-time living in mind, the Benchmark 42LFT offers residential luxury and smart functionality in a spacious destination trailer. Featuring dual loft spaces, triple slide-outs, and designer finishes throughout, this model is ideal for families, couples, or anyone who wants a true home-on-wheels experience.

Top Features of the Benchmark 42LFT

Spacious Double Loft Area

  • Three Bunk Mats in the upper loft—perfect for kids or guests

  • Wardrobe Storage for extra organization

  • A fun and functional second level that maximizes vertical space

Private Rear Bedroom

  • Power Tilting King Bed for custom comfort while sleeping, reading, or watching TV

  • Wardrobe & Dresser with a 32" TV included

  • Stackable Washer & Dryer make full-time living simple and convenient

Residential Kitchen with Island

  • Large Kitchen Island offers expanded prep space and a deep sink

  • Samsung 110V Refrigerator, residential range, microwave, and pantry storage

  • Perfect for cooking full meals or entertaining guests

Comfortable Front Living Room

  • Dual Recliner Theater Seats for movie nights or afternoon naps

  • 50" HDTV with Fireplace for warmth and ambiance

  • Hidden Storage for books, games, or travel accessories

Dual Entry Doors

  • Easy access from both ends of the trailer for added convenience

Spacious Full Bathroom

  • 48" x 30" Residential Shower, vanity, medicine cabinet, and linen closet

  • Luxury and practicality in one

Built for Comfort & Longevity

  • High-Gloss Fiberglass Exterior for a sleek, upscale look

  • Azdel Composite Sidewalls inside and out for enhanced insulation and durability

  • Oversized Windows in all rooms for natural light and scenic views

  • Solid Surface Countertops and Hardwood Cabinetry throughout

All-Season Climate Control

  • 45,000 BTU Air Conditioning and 60,000 BTU Furnace for year-round comfort

  • MCD Roller Shades for privacy and light control in every room

Exterior Highlights

  • Powder-Coated Aluminum Ladder

  • Auxiliary LP Tank Hookup for grills or outdoor kitchens

  • Residential Garden Hose Hookup for easy water access at your site

units.details:
2026 Alliance RV Benchmark 44LFT destination trailer highlights

  • Two Full Bathrooms
  • Two Lofts 
  • Washer/Dryer 
  • Dual Fireplaces
  • L-Shaped Sofa

 

This destination trailer is perfect for a big crowd since it has one Power Tiling king bed, three mattress and an L- shape sofa where 10 people can easily fit. Experience the in-home feeling with the amazing kitchen and living room, furnished with a Kitchen island, L- shape sofa and a residential 110 V fridge. Also, you can sense the extreme coziness thanks to the dual fire places and get 24/7 entertainment due to the four TVs along the trailer. Plenty of place can be found in the front and rear loft bedrooms with three wardrobes in total. Lastly the two full bathrooms will allow you to comfortably take a shower after a long day.

 

With any Benchmark destination trailer by Alliance RV, you will enjoy luxury features at every turn! The high gloss fiberglass exterior is ultra sleek, and the Azdel composite fiberglass sidewalls add durability so you can camp for years to come. You'll also find a residential exterior garden hose connection outside, along with a powder coated aluminum rear ladder, and an auxiliary LP tank hook up if you want to bring your grill along. Head inside to find hardwood cabinetry, solid surface countertops throughout, oversized windows in all rooms, and MCD roller shades throughout. The 45,000 BTU A/C and 60,000 BTU furnace will keep you comfortable year around, and there is a stackable washer and dryer to make full-time RV living easier than ever!

units.details:
Forest River Flagstaff Shamrock expandable 23IKSS highlights:

  • Two Tent End Beds
  • Kitchen island
  • Dual Slide Outs
  • 60" Sofa
  • Kitchen Island

 

Imagine hiking the trails, running around the campgrounds, and sitting by the campfire at your favorite state park with all your camping friends.  Now imagine being able to make your own meals, serve dinner inside on the kitchen island when it's raining, and falling asleep on your own tent end bed or on the furniture once converted into sleeping space.  This model is perfect for a couple who enjoys their own space as well as a family of six.  It's time to start checking off your bucket list, and start traveling today!

 

The Forest River Flagstaff Shamrock is exactly what you should take a look at when searching for the ideal expandable.  Each unit uses Easy Lube axles and Nev-R adjust brakes, plus a Torsion axle, and Rubber-Ryde suspension for a smooth tow to your destination.  Inside you will enjoy solid surface kitchen countertops, all the appliances necessary to make meals on the go, a bed cable system with no poles, a heated mattress on select models, and a WiFi Ranger WiFi Booster Sky 4 to mention a few reason you will love any expandable you choose!

Forest River Sierra Luxury fifth wheel 39BARK highlights:

  • Rear Separate Kitchen
  • Dual-Sink Vanity
  • Free-Standing Table
  • Hide-A-Bed Sofas
  • Fireplace
  • Pass-Through Storage

 

The front bedroom on this Sierra Luxury fifth wheel has a king bed slide for added space and comfort as well as a full-width mirrored wardrobe for extra convenience as you get ready each morning. The bedroom is right next to the full bathroom which has a dual-sink vanity for two people to get ready at once, a shower with seat, toilet, and linen closet. The living area is quite comfortable too with its two tri-fold hide-a-bed sofas and theater seating across from a fireplace and 50" flat screen LED HDTV. The kitchen is another area you'll favor because of the four-burner range, pantry, 22-cubic foot refrigerator, microwave, and free-standing table with chairs. And if you prefer not to let smelly foods cook inside, you can just go outside and use the exterior bumper-mount swivel gas grill to cook.

 

Are you looking to add a little glamour to your camping life? The Forest River Sierra Luxury fifth wheels are luxury units that bring all the fun. These models have an Underbelly Armor, a friction-hinge entry door, an exterior docking station, a high-gloss gel-coat fiberglass exterior, a six-point hydraulic leveling system, and high-efficiency radiant foil for the roof and floor. The interior is stylish and modern with its stainless steel appliances, decorative backsplash, rustic wood plank linoleum, handmade cabinetry, crown molding over the kitchen cabinets, and recessed residential lighting. There is a satellite and cable hookup as well as a King Wi-Fi extender system, and the premium sound bar with built-in flush-mounted DVD player will be great to have when you want to watch a movie.

Jayco North Point fifth wheel 365RKTS highlights:

  • Spacious Rear Kitchen
  • L-Shaped Sofa
  • Two Power Awnings
  • Shower with a Seat
  • Bedroom Closet with Drawers

 

You can't go wrong when camping in this triple slide out fifth wheel! Once you've arrived at your destination and unloaded the pass-through storage, you can make lunch in the rear kitchen with generous counter space. There are also two pantries, one being a pull-out, plus a convenient pull-out butcher block so you can chop fresh veggies! You can enjoy your meal at the roll-top dinette with chairs, and if you need to get some work done, the desk/coffee bar will provide a space for your laptop. An L-shaped sofa and theater seat in the main living area will create an inviting space, plus there is a 65" TV and a mantle with a fireplace just like at home! Freshen up in the full bath at the end of the day, then head to the front private bedroom for a great night's rest on the king bed slide out. There is a closet with drawers and a hamper below, a chest with a TV, plus washer and dryer prep for the option to add these appliances; how convenient!

 

With any North Point fifth wheel by Jayco you begin with a strong foundation with a custom frame, designed and sized specifically to best support each unit. Constructed with Stronghold VBL™ aluminum framed, vacuum bond laminated walls and the Magnum Truss™ XL6™ roof system with a one-piece, seamless roof material, which is the strongest tested roof in the industry. The 5-Star Handling package is included with Uniroyal tires, a MORryde rubber pin box, Dexter axles with Nev-R-Adjust brakes, MORryde CRE-3000 rubberized suspension and wet bolt fasteners and bronze bushings. The interior has handcrafted hardwood glazed doors and drawers, vinyl flooring throughout, an integrated under-mount sink in the main bathroom, plus so much more you just have to see one to believe it all!

Jayco Pinnacle fifth wheel 32RLTS highlights:

  • Walk-In Shower with a Seat
  • Kitchen Island
  • Tri-Fold Sofa
  • Shoe Garage
  • Exterior TV

 

Trips to the lake are made comfortable in this triple slide out fifth wheel. Once you arrive at the campground, set up the two power awnings with LED lights, and there is an exterior TV for the big game. Head inside to relax on the theater seats directly across from the TV and fireplace, or play a game at the roll-top dinette. The chef of your group will love this kitchen with its residential refrigerator, kitchen island, and pantry, plus additional storage for canned goods or paper products. The full bath will allow you to stay clean throughout your trip, and you'll find a residential style backsplash in the bath, plus a walk-in shower. Nothing says luxury like your own king bed slide out in the front bedroom, a large front closet with hamper and drawers for wrinkle-free clothes, and a flip-up dresser featuring a 32" TV!

 

Each Pinnacle fifth wheel features Stronghold VBL lamination for the lightest, yet strongest construction in the RV industry. Some of the exterior conveniences you will appreciate are the Keyed-Alike lock system, the fully enclosed, universal docking center, and the 6-point hydraulic auto-leveling system for quick and easy set up. The 5 Star Handling Package will make towing a fifth wheel a walk in the park, and the two Whisper Quiet A/C units will keep you comfortable during the hot summer months. Inside, you'll enjoy the residential "Do it all" sink with pull-out kitchen faucet, glass rinse, and vegetable rinse, the handcrafted hardwood glazed cabinetry, the vinyl flooring throughout, plus many more comforts. units.description: New 2026 Wayfinder RV GO LITE BOULDERBACK 14
units.details:
2026 Go Lite Boulderback 14: Compact Camping with Big Benefits

 

The Go Lite Boulderback 14 toy hauler travel trailer offers the functionality of a full-size RV in a lightweight, compact design that’s easy to tow with an SUV. It’s an excellent choice for adventurers who want to explore the great outdoors without upgrading their vehicle or dealing with the challenges of towing a large camper.

 

Key Features of the Go Lite Boulderback 14

Spacious Interior:

Despite its compact size, the Go Lite Boulderback 14 provides impressive space. The fold-up Murphy bed and pop-out tent expand the interior, creating a roomy and comfortable environment. Keep the back ramp door open with the magnetic screen in place to let in a refreshing breeze and stay connected to nature.

 

Lightweight and Easy to Tow:

With a UVW of just 2,380 pounds, the Go Lite is exceptionally lightweight, making it towable by smaller vehicles like SUVs, compact trucks, and some capable minivans. With an exterior length of only 16'2", its compact design allows you to access tight camping spots that larger RVs simply can’t reach.

 

Full Kitchen:

The Go Lite’s kitchen is thoughtfully designed to bring the comforts of home on the road. It features an 4.4-cubic-foot refrigerator and freezer, a full-sized residential farmhouse sink, a microwave, and a 2-burner stove, making cooking easy and enjoyable.

 

Adventure-Ready Design:

Built on a custom chassis tailored to its floorplan, the Go Lite Boulderback 14 offers extra support where it’s needed most. With an adjustable axle and heavy-duty off-road tires, this toy hauler is ready to take on rugged terrain and go wherever your adventures lead.

 

Why Choose Go Lite?

Go Lite redefines lightweight travel trailers, making adventure accessible to everyone. Weighing as little as 2,000 pounds, Go Lite trailers can be towed by most SUVs, V6 vehicles, and even minivans. Unlike other compact RVs, Go Lite combines affordability and functionality with essential features like a full kitchen, bathroom, and smart storage solutions. With Go Lite, you can embark on every adventure without compromise.

Spacious Interior:

Built on a custom chassis tailored to its floorplan, the Go Lite Mountainback offers extra support where it’s needed most. With adjustable axles and heavy-duty off-road tires, this toy hauler is ready to take on rugged terrain and go wherever your adventures lead.

 

At Wayfinder RV, our mission is to design RVs that our customers truly love. We listen to real RVers like you to build smarter, more comfortable, and more capable campers.

units.details:
2025 Go Lite Skybreaker: Tiny Trailer, Huge Experience

 

The Go Lite Skybreaker 12 travel trailer offers the functionality of a full-size RV in a lightweight, compact design that’s easy to tow with an SUV. It’s an excellent choice for adventurers who want to explore the great outdoors without upgrading their vehicle or dealing with the challenges of towing a large camper.

 

Key Features of the Go Lite Skybreaker 12

Spacious Interior:

The Go Lite Skybreaker 12 may be compact, but it’s loaded with features you'd expect in a much larger trailer. It comes equipped with a full kitchen, a dinette, a dry bath, a bunk bed, and a tent bed—providing three separate sleeping areas. You'll also enjoy tons of storage and panoramic windows that keep you connected to the great outdoors. It’s an awesome little model built for big adventures.

 

Lightweight and Easy to Tow:

With a UVW of just 2,300 pounds, the Go Lite is exceptionally lightweight, making it towable by smaller vehicles like SUVs, compact trucks, and some capable minivans. With an exterior length of only 13'10", its compact design allows you to access tight camping spots that larger RVs simply can’t reach.

 

Full Kitchen:

The Go Lite’s kitchen is thoughtfully designed to bring the comforts of home on the road. It features an 4.4-cubic-foot refrigerator and freezer, a full-sized residential farmhouse sink, a microwave, and a 2-burner stove, making cooking easy and enjoyable.

 

Adventure-Ready Design:

Built on a custom chassis tailored to its floorplan, the Go Lite Skybreaker 12 offers extra support where it’s needed most. With an adjustable axle and heavy-duty off-road tires, this trailer is ready to take on rugged terrain and go wherever your adventures lead.

 

Why Choose Go Lite?

Go Lite redefines lightweight travel trailers, making adventure accessible to everyone. Weighing as little as 2,000 pounds, Go Lite trailers can be towed by most SUVs, V6 vehicles, and even minivans. Unlike other compact RVs, Go Lite combines affordability and functionality with essential features like a full kitchen, bathroom, and smart storage solutions. With Go Lite, you can embark on every adventure without compromise.

units.description: New 2025 Wayfinder RV GO EXPLORE X203
units.details:
2025 Go Explore X203: Premium Camping, Practical Features

 

The Go Explore X203 couples camper delivers an effortless camping experience with premium, practical features--without the premium price tag. It's an ideal choice for couples seeking both comfort and functionality in their RV, empowering you to focus on what matters most: exploring, making memories, and enjoying the journey with confidence.

Key Features of the Go Explore X203

Smarter Storage Solutions:

The industry-exclusive Super Suite bedroom in the Go Explore is a game-changer, featuring an under-bed storage system to keep all your belongings organized. The spacious pass-through storage compartment includes thoughtful additions like pegboards, a fishing rod holder, and more, making organizing effortless.

 

Practical Camping Features:

Go Explore travel trailers offer convenient camping features such as a dedicated trash can space, a laundry chute in the bedroom with a collapsible laundry basket, and strategically placed coat hooks and storage racks. On the exterior, two Kebloc hooks with attachments for an outdoor trash bag holder and towel rack help keep your RV space tidy and functional.

 

Chef's Kitchen:

The Go Explore's kitchen brings the comforts of home to the road. Features include a residential-sized farmhouse sink, removable sink covers, a built-in spice rack, knife storage, and a paper towel holder, making meal preparation while camping easy. 

 

Excellent Entryway:

Every Go Explore model features the industry's widest entry door, paired with an extra-large grab handle to make packing and unpacking easier. The solid steps include industry-exclusive built-in shoe storage, ensuring your shoes stay organized rather than cluttering your RV or campsite.

 

Pet-friendly Design:

Go Explore's pet friendly design means traveling with your pets is easier. It includes two exterior D-rings for securing pet leashes and a versatile pet rover station that can be mounted outside or brought indoors. The ventless and carpetless flooring makes cleaning up your RV quick and easy.  

 

Convenient Sanitation Station:

All your water and sewer hookups are conveniently located in one accessible area. The sanitation station includes a large storage box for hoses and gloves, along with an extra-wide tube for stowing your sewer hose. With everything in arms reach, it makes setting up and breaking down your campsite easier than ever.

 

Why Choose Go Explore?

Every Go Explore model is designed with intention, and every area of Go Explore RVs are made with the question, "How would someone actually use this, and how can we make it easier for them?"

We listened to real campers--people tired of digging through messy storage or wrestling awkward setups. We turned their frustrations into solutions: smart storage that keeps gear organized, comfort features that make every trip feel like home, and thoughtful innovations that make your trips effortless and stress-free. Go Explore ensures that you can enjoy your adventures with confidence and ease.

2026 Go Play 20FBS: Affordable and Practical Camping

Go Play travel trailers are designed for families and first-time RVers seeking a durable, affordable camper that combines the must-have comforts of home with a feature-packed, family-friendly design. With space-saving layouts and rugged construction, these campers make camping simple, safe, and budget-friendly—so you can focus on having fun in the great outdoors.

 

Key Features of the Go Play 20FBS

 

Camp-Ready

 

We believe when you purchase an RV it should be Camp-Ready. That’s why every Go Play is equipped with a 200-watt solar package and a heated and enclosed underbelly, so you can enjoy the freedom to camp whenever and wherever adventure takes you. 

 

Built For Durability

 

Every Go Play is built with the industry leading Magnum Truss Roof™ system, protecting your RV from damage while you’re camping. The hardwood lumber core cabinets with 70 lb. rated, full extension ball-bearing drawer glides ensure your RV is built with long-lasting durability.

 

Spacious, Functional Interiors

 

With an 8-foot-wide design and 6'9" ceilings, the Go Play provides more headroom and living space than many other conventional built travel trailers. Smart storage solutions and added features like coat and towel hooks, and a dedicated wastebasket space make every Go Play interior functional.

 

Tried and True

 

The 10 floor plans in the Go Play lineup cover over 70% of the industry’s best-selling floor plans, meaning you don’t have to worry whether every Go Play is a proven, customer-approved model. By sticking to tried and true floor plans we save on development costs for new designs you might not love—and pass those savings directly to you.

 

Super Suite Bedroom (available only in the 20FBS, 22MLS, 26BH, 26BHS, & 26RLS)

 

The Super Suite bedroom provides a more functional bedroom space. The bed utilizes 2 gas struts to lift, revealing 4 extra drawers, shoe storage, and an open space with a laundry basket to put your dirty laundry underneath the bed.

 

Why Choose Go Play?

 

Go Play was built by people who love camping and designed based on our experience and years of customer feedback. 

 

With a Go Play travel trailer, you’ll have everything you need to focus on what matters most—spending time with the people you love and creating memories that last a lifetime.?

2026 Go Lite Solo: Simple and Camp Ready Rig for the Solo Adventurer

 

The Go Lite Solo travel trailer offers the functionality of a full-size RV in a lightweight, compact design that’s easy to tow with an SUV. It’s an excellent choice for adventurers who want to explore the great outdoors without upgrading their vehicle or dealing with the challenges of towing a large camper.

 

Key Features of the Go Lite Solo

Practical Design:

The innovative design of the Go Lite Solo provides an impressive amount of practical camping features that you won't find in other RVs of this size. Outside the Solo, you'll find a full kitchen, inside it is simply your sleeping solution and smart storage solutions. Get ready to get on the road!

 

Lightweight and Easy to Tow:

With a UVW of just 1,793 pounds, the Solo is exceptionally lightweight, making it towable by smaller vehicles like SUVs, compact trucks, and some capable minivans. Built on a custom chassis tailored to its floorplan, the Go Lite Solo offers extra support where it’s needed most. With an adjustable axle and heavy-duty off-road tires, this travel trailer is ready to take on rugged terrain and go wherever your adventures lead.

 

Why Choose Go Lite?

Go Lite redefines lightweight travel trailers, making adventure accessible to everyone. Weighing as little as 2,000 pounds, Go Lite trailers can be towed by most SUVs, V6 vehicles, and even minivans. The Go Beyond LTD 171FD travel trailer offers the functionality of a full-size RV in a lightweight, compact design that’s easy to tow with an SUV. It’s an excellent choice for adventurers who want to explore the great outdoors without upgrading their vehicle or dealing with the challenges of towing a large camper. Keep in mind, these are our limited series, a prototype run that allows us to try out all of the suggestions that you have for better RVs. This is a very limited run, and once they're gone, they're gone. 

 

Key Features of the Go Beyond LTD 171FD

Innovative & Practical Design:

The innovative design of the Go Beyond LTD 171FD provides an impressive amount of practical camping features that you won't find in other RVs of this size. Inside the Go Beyond, you'll find a full kitchen with a dinette, unique bathroom, dedicated queen bed, and loads of storage. 

 

Lightweight and Easy to Tow:

With a UVW of just 2,646 pounds, the 171FD is lightweight, making it towable by smaller vehicles like SUVs, compact trucks, and some capable minivans. With an exterior length of only 24", its not too long and allows you to access tight camping spots that larger RVs simply can’t reach.

 

Full Kitchen:

The Go Beyond’s kitchen is thoughtfully designed to bring the comforts of home on the road. It features a 4.4-cubic-foot refrigerator and freezer, a microwave, and a 2-burner stove, making cooking easy and enjoyable.

 

Adventure-Ready Design:

With strong wheel-wells and heavy-duty off-road tires, and an onboard 100W solar panel to recharge your batteries off-grid, this travel trailer is ready to take on rugged terrain and go wherever your adventures lead.

Tons of Storage

 

The Go Beyond LTD 171FD has an amount of storage that is unparallel. Spanning most of the length of the RV, you can fit brooms, fishing pools, totes, anything that you need to make camping memorable.

units.description: New 2026 Modern Buggy RV Big Buggy BB16
units.details:
Modern Buggy RV Big Buggy teardrop trailer BB16 highlights:

  • Wet Bath
  • Front Two Side Windows
  • Front Window
  • Large Refrigerator
  • Bunk Bed

 

If you're looking for a teardrop trailer with a little more sleeping space, check out this Big Buggy BB16! There is a front U-shaped dinette that can convert to cozy sleeping space, along with a 78" x 36" upper bunk, a two burner stove, and a large refrigerator for food. You can clean up each day in the wet bath that includes a two way bath vent fan plus a Dometic toilet. The exterior baggage door will keep all your gear secure, and the torsion axle will provide smooth towing from home to campground. 

 

With the Big Buggy teardrop trailer by Modern Buggy RV, you will have all-terrain tires with 14" ground clearance allowing you to venture on bumpy, muddy and off-the-beaten path roads. They are full of modern amenities including an A/C and furnace, a large refrigerator, an on-demand water water, plus convenient storage spaces. These models are built on a high quality strength, custom aluminum frame, and are put together with AZDEL ceiling and walls. Get out and explore today with the Big Buggy in tow!

Airstream Interstate 24GT Class B diesel motorhome Std. Model highlights:

  • Built-In Workstation
  • Power Rear Sofa
  • Wet Bath
  • Two LED HDTVs
  • Air Ride Suspension

 

Get ready to drive and stay in comfort and luxury in this motorhome with everything you need and everything you didn't even know you wanted! The driver and passenger seats swivel to face the interior living space allowing you to utilize the Corian countertop with an LED TV above to place your beverages and the driver can work from here if needed once stopped. Whip up a meal using the galley kitchen featuring a two-burner gas stove, and a large stainless steel sink and faucet, plus extra counter space for food prep. There is a 1.2 cu. ft. drawer microwave and deep drawers for storage, plus a slide-out pantry and a refrigerator with a freezer across from the sink. The power sofa in the rear can be fully flat with a push of a button so two can sleep or rest. And there is storage throughout for your hanging clothes, towels, luggage, dishes and more.

 

The Airstream Interstate 24GT Class B diesel motorhome offers comfort, performance and safety with the Mercedes-Benz Sprinter 3500 extended chassis, the 3.0L V6 turbo diesel engine, BlueTEC SCR technology, and Adaptive Electronic Stability Program. Also included: active blind spot, brake, driver attention, rear cross traffic assist, plus more safety features giving you peace of mind on the road. More standout features include the power-sliding side door for ease in entering and exiting with a built-in screen door to allow airflow when parked, storage cubbies with USB charging ports, and a super comfortable Ultraleather sofa that offers both seating and sleeping space. You will also appreciate the touch screen/touch pad electronic controls with an Energy Management system, and a 300 watt solar system for off-grid camping.
